      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 585: The MediaRecorder info callback calls stopAudioRecording(), which releases the recorder, but the dialog remains actionable. If the user then taps Send, stopAndSendAudioRecording() sends whatever file exists without knowing whether stopAudioRecording() succeeded or whether the recorder produced a finalized, valid file. This can send a truncated/corrupt audio file after max duration/filesize. Prefer routing the limit case through a single finalized state and disabling further recorder stop attempts. For example:\n```suggestion\nsetOnInfoListener { _, what, _ -\u003e\n    if (what \u003d\u003d android.media.MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_DURATION_REACHED ||\n        what \u003d\u003d android.media.MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_FILESIZE_REACHED) {\n        if (finishAudioRecording()) {\n            audioRecordDialog?.setMessage(getString(R.string.audio_recording_limit_reached))\n        } else {\n            cancelAudioRecording()\n            audioRecordDialog?.dismiss()\n            Toast.makeText(activity, R.string.audio_recorder_error, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\nwhere finishAudioRecording() stops/releases once and records whether the file is valid before allowing Send.",
